summaries.short: Lucas and Carrie enlist Fat Au in a last-ditch attempt to track down Job.
summaries.full: With new intel from Fat Au, Lucas and Carrie follow a Genoa lead in a last-ditch attempt to free Job, though the price is steep. Proctor finds that generosity sometimes goes unrewarded. Bunker finds a salve for his wounds, while a frustrated Calvin bristles under the yoke of an incarcerated master. Lucas pays the price for rescuing Rebecca from Boedicker.

titles.short: Innocent Might Be a Bit of a Stretch
titles.full: Innocent Might Be a Bit of a Stretch

summaries.short: Carrie strikes again; Bunker treads on thin ice; another grisly murder rocks Banshee.
summaries.full: Special Agent Veronica Dawson arrives in Banshee to investigate the serial murders and question Lucas. Carrie carries out her most ambitious strike yet against the Brotherhood. Cruz casts a suspicious eye on Bunker. Calvin is jolted when Randall Watts, the long-imprisoned skinhead leader and Proctor ally, ends up at the Bunkers' doorstep. Another grisly murder rocks Banshee.

summaries.short: Carrie embarks on a vigilante crusade; Brock eyes Lucas in the serial-murder case.
summaries.full: With her hunt for Job yielding no leads, Carrie vents her frustration by embarking on a vigilante crusade. A hillbilly meth dealer tempts fate by bringing his product into Banshee. Proctor reprimands Calvin for profiting from a seedy side business, and looks to expand his drug trade by partnering with a Colombian kingpin. Brock eyes Lucas in the serial-murder case.

titles.short: A Little Late to Grow a Pair
titles.full: A Little Late to Grow a Pair

summaries.short: Dawson and Lucas scope out an SM club in search of murder clues; Watts tests Calvin's limits.
summaries.full: Calvin is tested by Watts' mercenary partnership with Proctor, whose promise to the Colombians has taken a severe hit after the torching of his factory. Following separate leads in the serial-killer case, Dawson and Lucas converge in a members-only Goth club replete with painful SM initiation rites. Proctor, through Burton, sends a forceful message to his Amish kin.

summaries.short: Season Four Premiere. Lucas becomes immersed in a new Banshee crisis involving a vicious serial murderer.
summaries.full: Season Four Premiere. Haunted by his inability to locate Job following his abduction, Lucas returns to Banshee to find the town dramatically changed--with a new sheriff, a new mayor, and a serial murderer on the loose. Carrie, still guilt-ridden over the death of her husband Gordon, undergoes court-sanctioned therapy and looks to distract herself in familiar, violent, ways.

titles.short: Only One Way a Dogfight Ends
titles.full: Only One Way a Dogfight Ends

summaries.short: Lucas and Dawson narrow their search for a Satanist; Carrie's vigilantism has consequences.
summaries.full: With help from Lucas, Dawson narrows her search for Declan Bode, a Satanist 'person of interest' in Banshee's serial murders. An emboldened Calvin throws down a gauntlet to Proctor, and to Kurt. Carrie's recent vigilantism ends up putting both her and Deva in peril.

summaries.short: (Season Three Finale) Lucas and Gordon steel themselves for a bloody faceoff, as do Proctor and Rebecca.
summaries.full: (Season Three Finale) As Lucas recalls a secret chapter in his life, Job gets special treatment from a fan. Unexpectedly joined by Gordon, Lucas prepares to return to Genoa for a final negotiation with Stowe, or die trying. Proctor heads to Philly to settle a score. After a bloody denouement in Banshee, Brock finally gets what he's been wishing for.
